== Incidents ==
On 9 February 2017, a mechanical problem with a fan in the turbine hall of unit 1 caused an explosion and fire, causing five people to be treated for [[smoke inhalation]]. While the non-nuclear accident did not cause any radioactive leak, it did cause the number one reactor to be disconnected from the power grid.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/french-nuclear-power-plant-explosion-latest-injured-flamanville-la-manche-normandy-accident-fire-a7570876.html|title=French nuclear power plant explosion: 'Several injured' after blast in Flamanville |website= [[independent.co.uk]] |first= Lizzie |last= Dearden |date= 9 February 2017|access-date=9 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.ouest-france.fr/normandie/flamanville-50340/explosion-la-centrale-nucleaire-de-flamanville-des-blesses-4790646 |title= Incendie à la centrale nucléaire de Flamanville : ce que l'on sait |website= [[Ouest-France|ouest-france.fr]] |date= 9 February 2017|access-date=9 February 2017 |language= fr |trans-title=Fire at the Flamanville Nuclear Power Plant: What We Know}}</ref> EDF initially estimated the reactor would be operational within a week, but later estimated the end of March.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2017/feb/21/edf-faces-1m-a-day-bill-to-keep-french-nuclear-reactor-offline |title=EDF faces £1m a day bill to keep French nuclear reactor offline |first=Adam |last=Vaughan |newspaper=The Guardian |date=21 February 2017 |access-date=22 February 2017}}</ref>

Units 1 and 2 were under enhanced surveillance by regulator [[Autorité de sûreté nucléaire]] (ASN) from 2019 to 2022 because of shortcomings in some operating activities, a high number of maintenance faults, poor mastery of certain maintenance operations, and inadequate quality of the ten-year inspection documentation of unit 1. This involved about 30 ASN inspections a year.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.neimagazine.com/news/newsasn-lifts-its-enhanced-monitoring-of-flamanville-1-and-2-9832052/ |title=ASN lifts its enhanced monitoring of Flamanville 1 and 2 |publisher=Nuclear Engineering International |date=7 July 2022 |access-date=25 July 2022}}</ref>

